                            Box 1: The process for divisions

    Starting the division
    The Question is put, and voices are heard on both sides. The member on the
    Woolsack instructs the clerk to begin a division.
    The clerk enters the division information and launches the division. The pass-
    readers are activated and the voting period for eligible members starts. The
    clerk rises and bows to the member on the Woolsack.
    The member on the Woolsack rises and says: “Voting is now open. Clear the
    bar.”
    The doorkeepers sound the division bells, update the annunciator, and prepare
    the lobbies.
    First three minutes
    Tellers must be appointed within three minutes.
    Members can vote immediately, but are required to remain in the lobbies until
    Tellers are in place. Once Tellers are in place, the exits from the lobbies may be
    unlocked, and members pass the Tellers on their way out of the lobbies.
    If after three minutes no Tellers have been appointed for one or other side, the
    Question is decided in favour of the side which has appointed Tellers.
    If Tellers have been appointed, after three minutes the clerk bows to the member
    on the Woolsack, who repeats the Question and takes the voices. If there are
    voices on both sides, they then say: “The Contents will go to the right by the
    Throne. The Not-contents to the left by the Bar.”
    If there are no voices on one or other side, the Question is decided on the voices
    and the division is cancelled.
    During the division
    Members continue to pass through the lobbies, voting by tapping their passes,
    confirming that they have been registered by the pass-readers, and being
    counted by the Tellers at the end of each lobby.
    Members eligible for remote participation under SO 24A may vote on PeerHub.
    The clerk takes the votes of infirm members and of the member on the Woolsack
    (who will be required to present a valid security pass) and records their votes in
    the divisions system.
    Ending the division
    The PeerHub voting period for remote members expires automatically after
    eight minutes.
    At eight minutes, the clerk bows to the member on the Woolsack, who then
    repeats the Question without taking the voices. The doors into the Chamber are
    locked.
